}

<p class="firstclass secondclass thirdclass other class">WOAHHHHH</p>

@if (modelExample != null) {
    <div class="some thing any thing">
        <div class="containerthing">
            <p class="thing">Value A title</p>

            <p class="firstclass secondclass thirdclass other class">@(String.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(modelExample.ValueA) ? "Value A empty" : modelExample.ValueA)</p>
        </div>

        <hr class="dakine problem here why add a forward slash and space before less than symbol to fix">

        <div class="containerthing">
            <p class="thing">Value B title</p>

            <p class="firstclass secondclass thirdclass other class">@modelExample.ValueB</p>
        </div>

        <hr class="dakine problem here why add a forward slash and space before less than symbol to fix">

        <div class="containerthing" @onclick="@(() => Console.WriteLine("C clicked"))">
            <p class="thing">Value C title</p>

            @if (modelExample.ValueC == null) {
                <p class="firstclass secondclass thirdclass other class">VALUE C NULL</p>
            } else {
                <p class="firstclass secondclass thirdclass other class">@modelExample.ValueC</p>
            }
        </div>

        <hr class="dakine problem here why add a forward slash and space before less than symbol to fix">

        @Variable
    </div>
} else {
    <NavLink href="/place" class="firstclass secondclass thirdclass other class">anything goes here, "loading the model from server"</NavLink>
}

@code {
    [CascadingParameter]
    private Task<AuthenticationState> authenticationStateTask { get; set; }

    private TestModel modelExample = null;

    private bool Variable = false;

    //Nothing to see here

    protected async override Task OnInitializedAsync() {
        //just to have a method
        Console.WriteLine("testing");
        //API call for data
        modelExample = new TestModel() { ValueA = "[A]", ValueB = "[B]", ValueC = "[C]" };
        await Task.CompletedTask;
    }
}
```
using this model as the backing:
```C#
namespace TestingModel {
    public class TestModel {
        public string ValueA { get; set; }
        public string ValueB { get; set; }
        public string ValueC { get; set; }
    }
}
```

This triggers: RZ2005 (once per offending file) and CS0116 (sometimes multiple times per file) very consistently.

The solution is to either remove empty lines after `<hr>` elements or rewrite them to have a closing slash `<hr />`.

Shortened version by Ivan below (`@code {}` not required to trigger but will throw an additional error):
```C#
@page "/"

@if (true) {
    <div>
        <hr class="dakine problem here why add a forward slash and space before less than symbol to fix" >

    </div>
}
```

I am not sure if other self closing tags also trigger this or not, didn't test them but my project also didn't have errors from the other ones so it is possible but I am not sure.
